<P>
Show Goes On for Grateful Dead: The Grateful Dead will go ahead with planned 
shows despite the death last week of keyboard player Brent Mydland, and it is 
uncertain when a replacement for Mydland will be named. "It's possible that 
they'll start off (without a new member)," said publicist Dennis McNally of the 
tour that begins Aug. 31 with a three-night Bay Area stand in Mountain View and 
continues on the East Coast and in Europe. A report that Dead fan and friend 
Bruce Hornsby had been invited to join the band for some of the shows was 
labeled unfounded by both McNally and Hornsby's manager, Tim Neese. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
