<TEXT>
<P>
Cincinnati Bengal cornerback Lewis Billups will have to serve 30 days in jail 
for pointing a gun at two undercover police officers, a Cincinnati judge ruled. 
</P>
<P>
But because of a backlog in serving misdemeanor sentences, that probably will 
not happen until late January or early February, Hamilton County Common Pleas 
Judge Ralph Winkler ruled. 
</P>
