<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRUCE DAVIS JOINS RAIDERS IN LONDON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Offensive tackle Bruce Davis rejoined the Raiders Tuesday, after a two-year 
absence. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, who played for the Raiders from 1979-87, was traded to the Houston 
Oilers in 1988, where he played the last two seasons. He was waived by the 
Oilers in the off-season and signed with the Raiders as a free agent. He joined 
the team in London, where the Raiders will play the New Orleans Saints in an 
exhibition game Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders cut tackle John Layfield, a rookie free agent from Abilene 
Christian, to make room for Davis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
