BOLTON SULLIVAN; SKIL CORP. FOUNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bolton Sullivan, 94, a founder of Skil Corp., which produced the first portable 
electric saw. 
</P>
<P>
With his father, J. W. Sullivan, Bolton Sullivan founded Skil Corp. in 1924 in 
a one-room shop on Chicago's northwest side. The company manufactured and sold 
the Skilsaw, invented by Edmund Michel. The firm gained a worldwide reputation 
as a manufacturer of portable electric tools before it was merged into Emerson 
Electric Co. in 1979. In Lake Forest, Ill., on Thursday. 
