<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
PREGNANT L.B. WOMAN KILLED BY GANG GUNFIRE; BABY SURVIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pregnant Long Beach woman was killed by gang gunfire early today, but 
surgeons delivered her premature baby by emergency Cesarean section before she 
died early today, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Kentzie Pope, 31, was hit in the back by a shotgun blast fired from a passing 
car as she stood in front of an apartment building about 11:30 p.m. Tuesday, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Pope and several gang members were standing in front of the building, a known 
hangout for gang members, as the car passed, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics took Pope, who was eight months pregnant, to St. Mary Medical 
Center, where doctors delivered a premature baby girl by Cesarean section 
during emergency surgery, hospital spokeswoman Carolyn Cohen said. The baby 
weighed just over 4 pounds and is in critical condition, she said. 
</P>
