<TEXT>
<P>
The government should give special help to workers who lose their jobs because 
of policies on clean air, protecting the spotted owl and cutting defense, 
lawmakers said today. 
</P>
<P>
"As important as it is to reduce defense expenditures and to increase our drive 
to protect the natural environment, it is also important that we make every 
effort not to do so at the expense of American workers and their families," 
said Rep. Pete Stark (D-Oakland). 
