<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEL MAR; 
</P>
<P>
DOWN AGAIN TOPS THE FIELD IN BELLES RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six fillies and mares with serious turf portfolios will race at Del Mar 
Thursday afternoon in the $55,000 Belles for Mental Health purse. 
</P>
<P>
The race, which will be contested under allowance conditions, is scheduled to 
be run at a mile. 
</P>
<P>
Topping the cast for the feature is Down Again, a 6-year-old mare by Encino who 
sports a hefty bankroll that now reads at $578,021. The bay Kentucky-bred was 
last out July 11 at Hollywood Park, where she was beaten by less than a length 
on the turf by the Argentinian mare Jablina Brown, who scored here last 
Saturday in the Grade II Palomar Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
Corey Black has the call on Down Again Thursday at top weight of 122 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Here's the full field for the main event listed in post position order with 
their riders and weights: Triomphe, 116 pounds, Russell Baze the rider; Paper 
Princess, 118, Laffit Pincay Jr.; Formidable Lady, 120, Patrick Valenzuela; 
Down Again; Sonilla, 116, Eddie Delahoussaye, and Run To Jenny, 116, Gary 
Stevens. 
</P>
<P>
Formidable Lady has four wins, five seconds and two thirds from 18 starts for 
an earnings mark that has reached $246,175. Her most recent outing was in the 
same allowance race July 11 at Hollywood that Jablina Brown won. 
</P>
<P>
Paper Princess won the $107,600 Valkyr Handicap at Hollywood June 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
